title: The Grateful Dead: Jun. 10, 1973 at Robert F. Kennedy Stadium
description:
This is the official sound board recording of the 1973 performance of The Grateful Dead at Robert F. Kennedy Stadium. The files have been pulled from The Internet Archive&#039;s streaming-only section and labeled with proper ID3 tags. The show is divided into 31 tracks across 4 disks:

Disk 1
    Morning Dew
    Beat It On Down The Line
    Ramble On Rose
    Jack Straw
    Wave That Flag
    Looks Like Rain
    Box Of Rain
    They Love Each Other
    The Race is On
    Row Jimmy
    El Paso

Disk 2
    Bird Song
    Playin&#039; In The Band
    Eyes Of The World
    Stella Blue
    Big River

Disk 3
    Here Comes Sunshine
    Around & Around
    Dark Star
    He&#039;s Gone
    Wharf Rat
    Truckin&#039;
Disk 4
    Sugar Magnolia
    It Takes A Lot To Laugh It Takes A Train To Cry
    That&#039;s Alright Mama
    Promised Land
    Not Fade Away
    Goin&#039; Down The Road Feelin&#039; Bad
    Drums
    Not Fade Away
    Johnny B. Goode


Encoding: MP3 VBR (~200kpbs) at 41,000KHz
Total Running Time: 4 hours, 35 minutes
Original Internet Archive stream: http://www.archive.org/details/gd73-06-10.sbd.hollister.174.sbeok.shnf

If you like this comment to let me know what other kinds of shows you&#039;d like me to pull from the Archive. Keep on truckin&#039;.
